Deputy President David Mabuza is answering oral questions in the National Assembly on, among others, the state of investor confidence in SA's  economy. CAPE TOWN - Deputy President David Mabuza is answering oral questions in the National Assembly on the state of investor confidence in the South African economy, the measure to hold public enterprises directors to account and his efforts to make sure ministers attend scheduled meetings with parliamentary committees. WATCH: David Mabuza Q&A in Parliament 